oned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w/></mentioned>) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w/></mentioned>) </note><w>bunčuk</w> <gloss><q>a flock from horse tail attached to the standard</q></gloss></mentioned>. Probably, the following words: <mentioned xml:lang="tg"><lang/> <w>bunča</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>bənča</w> <gloss><q>bunch</q></gloss></mentioned> also belong here, by the meaning = <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>dasta</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Климчицкий._Вах."/></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Климчицкий._Вах."/></bibl>)</note></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>